				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$U^{A}(t)+U^B(t)$$\end{document} and the known universe energy \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$${\langle {H}\rangle }$$\end{document} becomes arbitrarily large if either of the initial populations gets close to the singular point \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
